                 USGS Mine Drainage Interest Group: Mission

  The mission of the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) Mine Drainage Interest Group
  (MDIG) is to promote communication, cooperation, and collaboration among USGS
  scientists working on problems related to mining and the environment. The
  group is interdisciplinary and includes members from all four program
  divisions of the USGS: Water Resources, Geologic, Biological Resources, and
  National Mapping.
